#: ../../P/pseudo.rst:5
msgid "pseudo"
msgstr "pseudo"

#: ../../P/pseudo.rst:7
msgid "/soo´doh/, n\\."
msgstr "/soo´doh/, 名詞"

#: ../../P/pseudo.rst:9
msgid "[Usenet: truncation of ‘pseudonym’]"
msgstr "[Usenet:‘pseudonym(偽名)’の短縮]"

#: ../../P/pseudo.rst:12
msgid ""
"An electronic-mail or :ref:`Usenet` persona adopted by a human for amusement"
" value or as a means of avoiding negative repercussions of one's "
"net.behavior; a ‘nom de Usenet’, often associated with forged postings "
"designed to conceal message origins. Perhaps the best-known and funniest "
"hoax of this type is :ref:`B1FF`\\. See also :ref:`tentacle`\\."
msgstr ""
"娯楽のため、あるいは自分のネット上の振る舞いの否定的な反響を避ける手段として、人間が採用する電子メールや\\ :ref:`Usenet`\\ "
"のペルソナ。‘nom de "
"Usenet’で、しばしばメッセージの出所を隠すために偽造された投稿に関連づけられる。おそらくこの種の最もよく知られ、最も可笑しい悪戯は\\ "
":ref:`B1FF`\\ である。\\ :ref:`tentacle`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../P/pseudo.rst:17
msgid ""
"Notionally, a :ref:`flamage`\\-generating AI program simulating a Usenet "
"user. Many flamers have been accused of actually being such entities, "
"despite the fact that no AI program of the required sophistication yet "
"exists. However, in 1989 there was a famous series of forged postings that "
"used a phrase-frequency-based travesty generator to simulate the styles of "
"several well-known flamers; it was based on large samples of their back "
"postings (compare :ref:`Dissociated-Press`\\). A significant number of "
"people were fooled by the forgeries, and the debate over their authenticity "
"was settled only when the perpetrator came forward to publicly admit the "
"hoax."
msgstr ""
"観念上、Usenetユーザを模倣する\\ :ref:`flamage`\\ "
"生成AIプログラム。必要なほどの洗練度のAIプログラムはまだ存在しないという事実にもかかわらず、多くのflamerが実際にそのような存在であると非難されてきた。しかし1989年に、フレーズ頻度に基づくtravesty"
" "
"generatorを使って数人の有名なflamerのスタイルを模倣した、有名な一連の偽造投稿があった。それは彼らの過去の投稿の大量のサンプルに基づいていた(\\"
" :ref:`Dissociated-Press`\\ "
"と比較せよ)。かなりの数の人々がその偽造に騙され、その真偽をめぐる論争は、犯人が悪戯を公に認めるために名乗り出てようやく決着した。"
